Repeated Sampling
Now we take many random samples of size 50 and calculate the mean for each sample.

set.seed(123)

sample_means &lt;- replicate(1000, {
  population |&gt;
    slice_sample(n = 50) |&gt;
    summarise(mean_value = mean(value)) |&gt;
    pull(mean_value)
})

sample_means_df &lt;- tibble(sample_mean = sample_means)

